WEBVTT

00:01.173 --> 00:03.075
Rent-A-Swag shareholders:

00:03.173 --> 00:07.075
As you can see,
your store is hoppin'.

00:07.110 --> 00:08.276
These kids are renting
my old clothes

00:08.294 --> 00:09.428
like they're going
out of style.

00:09.462 --> 00:10.712
Which they never will.

00:10.730 --> 00:12.480
Yeah, it's a lot
of foot traffic, Tommy.

00:12.498 --> 00:13.982
I like it.

00:14.000 --> 00:15.450
Oh, "day-yay-yam,"

00:15.468 --> 00:17.419
it is kind of
a sausage party in here.

00:17.437 --> 00:18.954
For the record,

00:18.988 --> 00:22.674
would hit it, would hit,
would hit.

00:22.725 --> 00:23.825
Hard pass.

00:23.860 --> 00:27.145
Tom, who is this... person?

00:27.180 --> 00:28.714
This is
Mona-Lisa Saperstein,

00:28.748 --> 00:29.948
my new sales associate.

00:29.999 --> 00:32.934
Mona-Lisa Saperstein?

00:32.968 --> 00:35.770
- Does that mean--
- ♪ Oh, yeah

00:35.788 --> 00:36.989
she's my sister.

00:37.023 --> 00:38.724
My twin sister,
from the same mister.

00:38.775 --> 00:40.792
Thank you so much
for hiring Mona-Lisa.

00:40.827 --> 00:41.843
It means so much to me.

00:41.878 --> 00:43.428
Even though,
honestly, she's...

00:43.479 --> 00:45.430
♪ The wo-o-orst.

00:45.481 --> 00:46.848
She is the worst person
in the world.

00:46.866 --> 00:48.033
Huge skank.
Terrible.

00:48.067 --> 00:49.785
But thank you.
It means a lot.

00:49.819 --> 00:51.536
Of course. Got to keep it
in the family.

00:51.571 --> 00:53.839
Yeah, but does it have to be
<i>this</i> family?

00:53.873 --> 00:55.290
Actually, that reminds me,

00:55.308 --> 00:56.625
Ba-ba-ba-boss man...

00:56.659 --> 00:57.826
I need to leave early today

00:57.860 --> 00:59.444
because my shrink
got me and him tickets

00:59.479 --> 01:01.513
to a Pitbull concert.

01:01.547 --> 01:03.165
And I already committed
to that.

01:03.199 --> 01:04.783
And so if you say
that I can't go,

01:04.816 --> 01:06.885
it's like you're taking
something away from me.

01:06.919 --> 01:08.453
Um, store's really busy.

01:08.488 --> 01:09.571
- I kinda need you to stay.
- Mmhmm.

01:09.605 --> 01:10.872
I totally hear you.

01:10.890 --> 01:12.391
Um, I also don't like
what you're saying.

01:12.425 --> 01:13.792
So if you say no,

01:13.826 --> 01:16.628
I <i>will</i> start a fire
in the bathroom.

01:17.162 --> 01:18.363
Okay, I guess you can go.

01:18.398 --> 01:20.365
Yeah, I know I can.

01:20.400 --> 01:21.516
What did I tell you, huh?

01:21.551 --> 01:25.971
♪ The wo-o-o-orst.

01:26.005 --> 01:27.389
She's the worst
in the world.

